		"description": "<p>Some scholars of occult matters take their quest for knowledge to dangerous extremes, mingling their own blood with that of otherworldly creatures to unlock deeper insights. Others so influenced by magical blood turn to scholarly pursuits to better understand and control what is happening to them. Your additional understanding grants you the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Intelligence score increases by 1.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with your choice of Arcana, Nature, History, or Religion, and an expertise die on any of these skills you are proficient with.</li>\n<li>When you make a check with one of the above skills that would benefit from your @UUID[Compendium.a5e-bloody-heretics.bloody-heretics.Item.eTY6NEUbkTEH3PHp]{Preternatural Awareness}, you may choose to shed some of your enchanted blood to read and draw upon for information. As a bonus action, you expend a hit die and roll it. You take damage equal to the resulting roll and your hit point maximum is reduced by that amount until you finish a long rest, but you gain an additional expertise die on the check, a bonus equal to your Intelligence modifier, and your maximum expertise die size is increased to a d12.</li>\n<li>As a bonus action, you may make a check with one of the above skills against a creature of the type related to your bloodblade archetype to mark them. The DC is 10 + the CR of the creature. On a success, you gain an expertise die on attack rolls against the marked creature for 1 minute, as well as any attempts to track them or locate them if hidden. You may shed some blood to gain the benefits of this feat on the check as part of the same bonus action.</li>\n<li>You may freely take any bloodblade @UUID[Compendium.a5e-bloody-heretics.bloody-heretics.Item.o8OLFET0ceh9GSWy]{Esoteric Art} whenever you would gain a @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.msqiaadyn4lilf8b]{Scholarly Discovery}, or a Scholarly Discovery anytime you would gain an Esoteric Art, and add half your scholar level to your bloodblade level for the purpose of Esoteric Arts and half your bloodblade level to your scholar level for the purpose of Scholarly Discoveries.</li>\n</ul>",
